          2. About us

            While studying abroad in a foreign country, I suffocated like a fish out of water in cafeteria conversations, and I looked forward to the emergence of a device that could dismantle the high walls of language but retain a human warmth.

            Merryking is not just about grammatical perfection, it's about conveying the warmth of communication. We dont just translate languages we translate trust.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          • CHRIS
            5.0 out of 5 stars AM05 smart watch review
            Reviewed in the United States on June 3, 2025
            Color: Black
            I mainly bought this watch to replace my fitbit versa 2, I was really only looking for something that could track my heart rate and sleep, also, a watch to tell time.

            So far, this has exceeded my expectations.

            It came out of the box fully charged, very simple setup process, and has a whole mess of features. The chatGPT feature is neat, it can really go into some detail depending on what you ask it. The translation feature is also really well done, my only complaint is that the languages are each written in their native dialect, so as someone who can't tell the difference between Japanese and Chinese text, I'm not sure I'm picking the right one for when I need it, but the small instances I have used it, works wonders.

            The interface is very snappy, and has alot of different pre build watch faces. You can make a custom one if you want, but I feel the presets all have a really cool look to them on their own. You can have a simple clock face, a digital read out, or you can clutter it up with the weather, heart rate, pedometer and other widgets if thats your thing.

            I have a galaxy s22, and it paired with no issue, syncs perfectly, and the phone answering functionality is top notch. The watch itself has a speaker and microphone, so you can do calls from it or you can listen/control music from your phone, even switch on the fly from there the music is coming from. I wear Bluetooth earbuds alot, it doesn't interfere with those at all, very seamless and user friendly.

            For $129, and a brand I had never heard of, I wasn't too sure but I am VERY pleased with my purchase.

            Amazon Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
            I just got this Language Translation Earbuds, and I absolutely love them! They look super cool in black, and they feel light and comfy in my ears. First of all, these earbuds can translate 144 languages and accents. That number made me do a little happy dance when I read it. And they worked perfectly. I talked to my neighbor in their language l, and the translation popped up on the little touchscreen on the charging case. It was so fastI barely had time to blink! It really felt like I was talking to a real person who spoke my language.
            The charging case is really smart, too. It has a 2.01inch LCD touchscreen that shows the battery life and lets me control the earbuds without having to use my phone. I can swipe to play music, answer calls, or even see song lyrics right on the screen. Plus, the case has a remote camera control button that lets me take selfies from far away. My friends were so impressed when I snapped a picture without touching my phone. I also love that there are three ways to use them in different situations. In Free-Speech Mode, each person wears one earbud, and its like youre just talking normally. In Speaker Mode, you pop both earbuds in or use your phone speaker for quick chats, like asking for directions at a coffee shop. Touch Mode is really neatif you tap your earbud, the other person hears your words translated in their ear.
            The battery life is also amazing. Ive used them all daylistening to music, making calls, and translatingand I still had plenty of charge left. When I finally put them back in the case, they started charging right away.

            The Merryking AI language translator earbuds hook over my lobes like sporty Bluetooth headsets, leaving the ear canal open so I can still hear street noise. One tap in the companion app selects English Spanish; I speak, the bud spits back smooth Espaol before my coffee even cools. During a farmers-market run I bargained for fresh tamales without butchering accent marks, and the vendors grin said it all.

            Latency sits around a second, short enough that conversations flow instead of stagger. At work I flip to lecture mode, toss one earbud to a visiting engineer from Tokyo, and the device handles tech jargon between English and Japanese like its flexing an engineering degree.
